   Program Summary: Program Direction

   Vision Statement
   Crops and landscapes protected from plant diseases using scientifically
   based, environmentally sound, and cost-effective methods

   Mission Statement
   Develop control strategies to reduce losses caused by plant diseases
   that are effective and affordable while maintaining environmental
   quality.

   Research Components
     * Identification and Classification of Pathogens
     * Biological Control
     * Cultural Control
     * Pathogen Biology, Genetics, Population Dynamics, Spread, and
       Relationship with Hosts and Vectors
     * Host Plant Resistance to Disease
